<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=2115&amp;p=17924#p17924"><![CDATA[
(rewriting question...)<br />Does any game which uses 8k of CHR RAM <strong>(and no other chr ram/rom)</strong> do CHR bankswitching within the 8k?  It would be quite silly to do so, since it's just rearranging the same memory into a different configuration, but do any games do it?  The Waixing DQ4 pirate breaks if you emulate the MMC3 CHR bankswitching to change the mapping of CHR ram.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=53">Dwedit</a> — Fri Sep 22, 2006 9:58 pm</p><hr />
